            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Most pathetic and worst school to work in. I come with a ten year long experience and to be honest I found the gujjus here to be the most unprofessional. The school is run by bunch of illiterates who shows off great opulence without an iota of intelligence. If you are being promised with a lot of facilities and you think you will join as a teacher, then I would request you to re think your decision. They will never pay you on time. There's terrible work politics. The owner is dumb, the coordinators run an alian drama with no grip over their subject, the Principal is a showpiece of activity that conspires into \"nothing\" and oh yes they have long treacherous hours of duty from 7.30am to 8pm and during school occasions, sports, functions than the duty hours begin from 7.30am to 1.30am midnight. Ah yes midnight, you read that right. There's no market nearby, travel is a big time hindrance. Gujjus look down upon people from other states, very pathetic work environment where you will be treated with disrespect every moment. I earned love, I earned warmth too but with a ten years teaching experience around different cities, this GIS will remain one of the biggest nightmares, a school that isn't just a school but can be happily compared to the slaughter house of Germany. ",
